    <section id="about">
        <h2>About Me</h2>
        <p>Hello! I am a PhD scholar at the <strong>Shock Wave and Impact Research Laboratory</strong>, Department of Civil Engineering, IIT Guwahati, under the guidance of Dr. Vivek Padmanabha. My research focuses on <strong>impact and shock dynamics</strong> in rock engineering and mechanics, especially fragmentation processes and the effects of high strain rates. I aim to enhance the understanding of rock and brittle geomaterials under extreme conditions, contributing to innovative solutions in mining and civil engineering.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="research">
        <h2>Research Interests</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Impact and shock dynamics</li>
            <li>Rock engineering and mechanics</li>
            <li>Fragmentation processes</li>
            <li>High strain rate effects</li>
            <li>Brittle geomaterials behavior</li>
            <li>Mining and civil engineering applications</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

